<main id="content" class="content"> <header> <h1 class="title">The Sin of Ambivalence</h1>
 <p class="subtitle" role="doc-subtitle">Jan 12, 2017 00:00</p>
</header> <p>
Holy God,
</p>

 <p>
The greatest tragedy <br></br>
is not to hate God, <br></br>
for the one who hates <br></br>
has God ever present <br></br>
before his mind.
</p>

 <p>
It is ambivalence, <br></br>
thoughtless and uncaring, <br></br>
a life that is at once <br></br>
both full and empty, <br></br>
full of trivialities, <br></br>
yet empty of meaning
</p>

 <p>
Heal my lukewarm heart, Lord, <br></br>
and restore me to my first love.
</p>

 <p>
 <i>Amen</i>
</p>


